International Executive Recruiter - (Visa sponsorship provided) - SingaporePosted 6 days agoExperienceMid-Senior levelJob functionHuman ResourcesEmployment typeFull-timeIndustryAirlines/AviationJob ID13591436This is a preview of the International Executive Recruiter - (Visa sponsorship provided) job at Aviation Labour Group. To view the full job listing, join LinkedIn - its free!Join LinkedIn - its free!About this jobJob descriptionInternational Executive Recruiter - Singapore For suitably qualified international candidates ALG will provide; visa sponsorship, relocation and an expatriate remuneration package. Aviation Labour Group has a fantastic opportunity for an International Executive Recruiter to be based in our Singapore Office. The prime responsibility of the role is to identify and develop new clients, subsequently placing Executives and permanent staff into the International Aviation industry. You will be responsible for the growth of the billing client base of ALG internationally. Since 2004 Aviation Labour Group has established itself as a leader in the recruitment of Aviation personnel in casual, contract and permanent placements across Australia, New Zealand and Asia. ALG has developed recruitment procedures that are fully accredited to the ISO 9001:2008 Quality Management Systems standard. Through our expert recruiters ALG can provide staffing solutions to all departments and required skill sets in the Aviation Industry. KEY RESPONSIBILITIES AND ACCOUNTABILITIES
· Identification of key personnel within industry and ability to interview and market these candidates out to suitable clients within the international aviation industry.
· Generation of revenue through the selection and recruitment of suitable candidates into vacant positions with international clients.
· Following ALG’s recruitment and selection processes to ensure that clients and candidates are fully compliant. This is achieved through screening, interviews, reference checks and obtaining suitable qualifications / documentation.
· Growth in new accounts, all revenue streams and market share. · Maintain, enhance and create awareness of ALG’s brand, reputation and strengths in the market place.
· Lead business development activities. Research and understand the division of prospective clients to develop appropriate sales strategies.
· Acquire profitable clients at agreed target margin or greater; and manage the preparation of tenders as required.
· Develop and implement sales plans, as well as relationship and account management strategies that result in business growth and penetration of new business markets/ industries.
· Provision of high value, quality solutions that address the client’s strategic business needs which meet or exceed time and quality expectations.
· Maintain awareness of competitive trends and activities in the Aviation market, and take action to mitigate threats.
· Identification and minimisation of business risks for ALG. Resolve and document client issues/ concerns, and when required seek support and assistance for resolution.
· Seek referral business from key contacts and identify new areas of opportunity by expanding on client relationships.
· Work with Management team in the implementation of strategies, plans and business solutions as required.
· Provide statistical information to Management on matters such as vacancy and future manning level status reports; highlighting any potential issues and recommended solutions. CORE COMPETENCIES
1. Demonstrated ability to network and build relationships at various levels. Detailed knowledge of recruitment and the aviation Industry.
2. Understanding and/or demonstrated experience in business development. An aptitude for sales and a demonstrated ability to negotiate and secure business
3. Understanding and working knowledge of the Quality Management System; business processes and their importance.
4. Well-developed verbal and written communication skills. Good knowledge of commercial contracts. EDUCATION AND/OR QUALIFICATIONS
Minimum degree qualified.
Appropriate recruitment industry experience.Desired Skills and ExperiencePrevious recruitment experience and an interest in the aviation industry.About this companyAviation Labour GroupSince 2004 Aviation Labour Group has established itself as a leader in the recruitment of Aviation personnel in casual, contract and permanent placements across Australia, New Zealand and Asia. Through our expert recruiters Aviation Labour Group can provide staffing solutions to all departments and required skill sets in the Aviation Industry. Aviation Labour Group have developed recruitment procedures that are fully accredited to the ISO 9001:2008 Quality Management Systems standard, and with these recruitment procedures we are able not only to provide quality Aviation personnel but staffing solutions to other industries than can be closely connected to the Aviation industry. Aviation Labour Group also provides recruitment solutions for the defense forces of Australia and New Zealand. Our stringent recruitment and selection processes which includes, OH&S, document and identity verification, and testing,means we only manage your vacancies with suitably skilled, qualified, and experienced personnel.Similar jobsSingaporePosted 6 days agoSingaporePosted 13 days agoSingaporePosted 22 days agoSingaporePosted 12 hours agoSingaporePosted 25 days agoSingaporePosted 25 days agoSingaporePosted 13 days agoSingaporePosted 4 days agoSingaporePosted 14 days agoSingaporePosted 7 days agoThis is a preview of the International Executive Recruiter - (Visa sponsorship provided) job at Aviation Labour Group. To view the full job listing, join LinkedIn - its free!Join LinkedIn - its free!People also searchedPeople also viewedSingaporePosted 5 days agoSingaporePosted 4 days agoSingaporePosted 6 days agoSingaporePosted 13 days agoSingaporePosted 6 days agoSingaporePosted 4 days agoSingaporePosted 11 days agoSingaporePosted 7 days agoSingaporePosted 15 days agoSingaporePosted 4 days ago
